$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a1 = random(2,9,1);
$m1 = .5*$a1**(-1.5);
$y1 = $a1**(-.5);
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
The linear approximation at \( x=0 \) to
\(  \frac {1} { \sqrt { $a1 - x } } \) is \( A + B x \)
where \( A \) is: \{ans_rule(20) \}
EOT
$ans = $y1;
ANS(num_cmp($ans));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
and  where \( B \) is: \{ans_rule(20) \}
EOT
$ans = $m1;
ANS(num_cmp($ans));

